==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toadfish
<hw>Toad"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any marine fish of the genus <gen>Batrachus</gen>,
having a large, thick head and a wide mouth, and bearing some
resemblance to a toad. The American species (<spn>Batrachus tau</spn>)
is very common in shallow water. Called also <altname>oyster
fish</altname>, and <altname>sapo</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
angler.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A swellfish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toadflax</ent>⟦br⟧
